WEBVTT

00:00.987 --> 00:02.521
Behold, my fellow travelers.

00:02.522 --> 00:05.157
Today, we cross the winding straits

00:05.158 --> 00:09.126
to the rocky river
to the shores of Valencia.

00:09.128 --> 00:11.196
No, I wouldn't take the rocky river route.

00:11.197 --> 00:13.131
There are rumors of thieves and bandits.

00:13.132 --> 00:14.833
I don't care about bandits.

00:14.834 --> 00:18.636
I'm Galavant, and Galavant will
be deterred by no foe in his...

00:18.637 --> 00:20.638
Who ate all the raisins
out of the trail mix?

00:20.639 --> 00:22.774
I hate cashews, and Brazil nuts are gross.

00:22.775 --> 00:24.943
You know what?

00:24.944 --> 00:27.545
Heroes get the raisins.
And they choose the path.

00:27.546 --> 00:29.748
That's just the way it goes.

00:29.749 --> 00:33.017
Look, can we just hold it
together for a few more days?

00:33.018 --> 00:34.812
We've been doing so well, right?

00:34.814 --> 00:36.821
- Right.
- Right.

00:36.822 --> 00:38.623
♪ We eat together ♪

00:38.624 --> 00:40.124
♪ We drink together ♪

00:40.125 --> 00:43.094
♪ We work in perfect sync together ♪

00:43.095 --> 00:43.945
♪ We smile ♪

00:43.947 --> 00:45.130
- ♪ Frown ♪
- ♪ Blink ♪

00:45.131 --> 00:48.600
♪ Together completely ♪

00:48.601 --> 00:51.970
♪ We walk together, in time together ♪

00:51.971 --> 00:53.171
- ♪ Can't help ♪
- ♪ Yelp ♪

00:53.172 --> 00:54.939
- ♪ Kelp ♪
♪ But rhyme together ♪

00:54.940 --> 01:00.411
♪ Our voices chime together so neatly ♪

01:00.412 --> 01:03.948
♪ And togetherness is what we do ♪

01:03.949 --> 01:06.784
♪ Together, me and him and you ♪

01:06.785 --> 01:09.187
- ♪ Like rock ♪
- ♪ And scissors ♪

01:09.188 --> 01:11.422
♪ And paper ♪

01:11.423 --> 01:13.257
♪ And stuck together ♪

01:13.258 --> 01:14.592
♪ All day together ♪

01:14.593 --> 01:17.695
♪ We're in each other's way together ♪

01:17.696 --> 01:20.531
♪ Our quirks are on display together ♪

01:20.532 --> 01:23.234
♪ Or nearly ♪

01:23.235 --> 01:26.904
♪ But togetherness
will see us through ♪

01:26.905 --> 01:29.707
♪ Unless I kill the other two ♪

01:29.708 --> 01:32.844
♪ Or we kill her together ♪

01:32.845 --> 01:35.680
♪ But there's some things we don't share ♪

01:35.681 --> 01:40.017
♪ Like the way I've kind of
sort of totally played him ♪

01:40.018 --> 01:44.255
♪ Oh, God, I've betrayed him ♪

01:44.256 --> 01:47.725
♪ And there's some things we don't share ♪

01:47.726 --> 01:53.397
♪ Like I'm kind of sort of
always thinking about her ♪

01:53.398 --> 01:57.401
♪ Or like how you both ignore me
all of the... ♪

01:57.402 --> 01:59.904
♪ Each day together's
a chore together ♪

01:59.905 --> 02:01.972
- ♪ A belching ♪
- ♪ Nagging ♪

02:01.973 --> 02:03.374
- ♪ Bore ♪
♪ Together ♪

02:03.375 --> 02:06.744
♪ then listening to her
snore together ♪

02:08.413 --> 02:11.816
It's like she's a bear.

02:11.817 --> 02:15.319
♪ But together, though,
is what we'll be ♪

02:15.320 --> 02:18.289
♪ For what feels like eternity ♪

02:18.290 --> 02:19.824
- ♪ Together ♪
- ♪ Me ♪

02:19.825 --> 02:21.392
- ♪ And me ♪
- ♪ And me ♪

02:21.393 --> 02:24.295
♪ As one ♪

02:24.296 --> 02:26.931
♪ As one ♪

02:26.932 --> 02:30.334
♪ As one! ♪

02:30.335 --> 02:36.340
♪ As... ♪
♪ As o-o-o-one! ♪

02:36.341 --> 02:38.171
- That is so typical.
- What's typical?

02:38.173 --> 02:40.109
I thought you said I was gonna
have the big finish this time.

02:40.111 --> 02:41.345
It was supposed to be my turn afterwards.

02:41.346 --> 02:43.180
- It's never your turn.
- Well, no, that's...

02:44.349 --> 02:45.582
Bandits.

02:45.583 --> 02:48.685
- If only someone had warned us.
- Yeah, well, you snore.

02:49.752 --> 02:51.187
Galavant - 01x04
Comedy Gold

02:51.188 --> 02:53.188
<font color="#80ff80">sync and correction by solfieri
www.addic7ed.com</font>

02:56.855 --> 03:00.524
I've got something else
you can do with your hands.

03:04.029 --> 03:07.640
I cannot believe My Queen is
cheating on me with that joker.

03:07.642 --> 03:09.142
He's a jester, sir.

03:09.144 --> 03:10.801
I know he's a jester, Gareth.

03:10.802 --> 03:12.546
I was insulting him
by calling him a joker,

03:12.548 --> 03:14.439
like when you call someone a clown.

03:14.439 --> 03:17.541
- But people like clowns.
- Damn it, man! Would you just let me vent?!

03:19.062 --> 03:21.879
I think I know why Madalena
likes him more than me.

03:21.880 --> 03:23.848
He's funny.

03:23.849 --> 03:26.217
How do I compete with that?

03:26.710 --> 03:29.854
Well, funny's easy. I mean, I'm funny.

03:29.855 --> 03:30.888
Really?

03:30.889 --> 03:33.391
- Yeah. Knock, knock.
- Who's there?

03:33.392 --> 03:34.892
He's a  you  thing up

03:34.893 --> 03:36.961
you in the  chair

03:36.962 --> 03:38.629
with the  and knees

03:38.630 --> 03:42.366
is taking it
out that son

03:42.367 --> 03:43.701
Good Lord, Gareth.

03:43.702 --> 03:45.469
Do you kiss my ring with that mouth?

03:45.470 --> 03:47.371
My mum taught me that one.

03:47.372 --> 03:49.573
Oof.

03:51.376 --> 03:54.545
Now, if that fool is tickling
my wife's funny bone,

03:54.546 --> 03:56.714
it leaves me no choice.

03:56.715 --> 03:59.116
I know what I have to do.

04:04.823 --> 04:07.091
Hello, jester.

04:07.092 --> 04:09.526
Do you think I'm an idiot?

04:09.527 --> 04:15.499
I know precisely what you have
been doing with my wife.

04:15.500 --> 04:18.002
Aah!

04:19.170 --> 04:20.671
It's a bendy sword.

04:20.672 --> 04:21.839
Isn't that fantastic?

04:21.839 --> 04:23.774
Oh!

04:25.031 --> 04:26.777
Not even a giggle.

04:26.778 --> 04:30.881
See, this is precisely
why I need your help.

04:30.882 --> 04:32.683
Please teach me to be funny.

04:32.684 --> 04:34.318
I'm begging you.

04:34.319 --> 04:35.619
- Gah!
- Ohh!

04:35.620 --> 04:37.287
- Oh!
- Aah!

04:37.288 --> 04:40.390
Even when you know it
bends, you still think... whoa!

04:41.526 --> 04:44.661
Please tell me you hid the jewel.

04:44.662 --> 04:46.130
Of course I hid the jewel...

04:46.131 --> 04:48.098
In a place where no one will ever find it.

04:48.099 --> 04:50.534
Uh, excuse me. Where are you taking us?

04:50.535 --> 04:53.237
The pirate king will decide your fate.

04:55.840 --> 04:57.641
"I don't care what road we choose.

04:57.642 --> 04:58.809
I'm Galavant.

04:58.810 --> 05:00.898
- I get to eat the raisins."
- "I'm Isabella.

05:00.900 --> 05:03.347
I chew with my mouth open like
a cow working on a fresh cud."

05:03.348 --> 05:05.816
I have a deviated septum. I told you that.

05:05.817 --> 05:07.451
I can't breathe through my nose.

05:07.452 --> 05:09.753
If I chew with my mouth closed,
I'd get no air.

05:09.754 --> 05:10.888
Do you want me to die?

05:12.724 --> 05:14.224
Well...

05:14.225 --> 05:17.761
Wait. What are pirates doing
miles from the ocean?

05:22.567 --> 05:25.402
I'm... so sorry. Am I missing something?

05:25.403 --> 05:26.737
Where's your boat?

05:26.738 --> 05:30.540
I'll be asking the questions around here.

05:30.541 --> 05:32.309
Arr!

05:32.310 --> 05:34.277
Actually, go ahead.

05:34.278 --> 05:35.679
I didn't have a question ready.

05:35.680 --> 05:39.182
Um... don't you need a boat to be pirates?

05:39.183 --> 05:40.951
You're on land.

05:40.952 --> 05:43.820
- Land ho!
- Carl, stop it.

05:43.821 --> 05:47.457
All you need to be a pirate
is a dark heart

05:47.458 --> 05:50.227
and a wicked disregard
for other people's lives.

05:50.228 --> 05:51.528
And swords.

05:51.529 --> 05:54.531
Of course swords.
That goes without saying.

05:54.532 --> 05:56.500
Everyone knows pirates need swords.

05:56.501 --> 05:58.435
- What about a hook hand?
- Parrots? Peg legs.

05:58.436 --> 06:01.738
- Land ho!
- I said stop it!

06:01.739 --> 06:05.242
Maybe it'll be easier to explain
in a pirate shanty.

06:05.243 --> 06:07.911
♪ Ho ♪

06:07.912 --> 06:10.080
♪ Ho ♪

06:10.081 --> 06:12.215
♪ We're cruel and vicious pirate men ♪

06:12.216 --> 06:14.517
♪ As hard and tough as brass ♪

06:14.518 --> 06:16.519
♪ By far the fearsomest buccaneers ♪

06:16.520 --> 06:17.887
♪ To ever walk on grass ♪

06:17.888 --> 06:20.290
- ♪ We pillage here ♪
- ♪ And plunder there ♪

06:20.291 --> 06:22.459
♪ We rage from dusk till dawn ♪

06:22.460 --> 06:24.427
♪ we hoist the anchor
and swab the deck ♪

06:24.428 --> 06:26.229
♪ Then gather for drinks on the lawn ♪

06:26.230 --> 06:28.531
♪ We're the lords of the sea ♪

06:28.532 --> 06:30.333
♪ Except we aren't at sea ♪

06:30.334 --> 06:32.335
♪ We're the lords of the sea ♪

06:32.336 --> 06:34.137
♪ Just not of the actual sea ♪

06:34.138 --> 06:35.939
Arr...

06:35.940 --> 06:39.709
♪ Now, how we ended up here,
'tis a dire and dreadful tale ♪

06:39.710 --> 06:43.680
♪ The kind to leave the meanest
rogue a-puking o'er the rail ♪

06:43.681 --> 06:45.648
♪ So fateful, so accursed ♪

06:45.649 --> 06:48.051
♪ Such a stroke of evil luck ♪

06:48.052 --> 06:50.019
♪ our ship washed up
on that thar hill ♪

06:50.020 --> 06:51.578
♪ And hey, I guess it stuck ♪

06:51.580 --> 06:55.925
♪ so now we hold the river
here by brutal, violent force ♪

06:55.926 --> 06:58.194
♪ We've also taken up gardening ♪

06:58.195 --> 07:00.263
- ♪ Sustainably ♪
- ♪ Of course ♪

07:00.264 --> 07:02.232
♪ we make you pay to cross this way ♪

07:02.233 --> 07:04.367
♪ And squeeze you till it hurts ♪

07:04.368 --> 07:06.336
♪ And on the side, we sell a line ♪

07:06.337 --> 07:08.137
♪ Of homemade organic desserts ♪

07:08.138 --> 07:10.440
♪ We're the lords of the sea ♪

07:10.441 --> 07:12.008
♪ Though, technically, next to the sea ♪

07:12.009 --> 07:13.843
♪ We're the lords of the sea ♪

07:13.844 --> 07:22.719
♪ Or sort of "of the se-e-a"! ♪

07:25.022 --> 07:29.926
So, now we live here,
and we rob any passersby.

07:29.927 --> 07:32.395
- Which brings us back to you.
- Please, sir.

07:32.396 --> 07:35.298
We're merely poor travelers
with nothing worth taking.

07:35.299 --> 07:39.302
Hey, captain. Look what I found.

07:40.337 --> 07:42.672
Oh, for the love of g... in your purse?

07:42.673 --> 07:44.974
That's where you thought
no one would look for it?

07:44.975 --> 07:46.642
I put it with my girls' supplies.

07:46.643 --> 07:49.479
Guys never look there.
They must have sisters.

07:50.814 --> 07:55.284
Poor travelers, huh?
Well, what do we have here?

07:55.285 --> 07:56.452
It's a jewel.

07:56.453 --> 07:58.621
I know it's a jewe... you know what?

07:58.622 --> 08:00.456
You're having a time-out. Go to your tent.

08:00.457 --> 08:03.025
Don't you give me that look.

08:08.043 --> 08:10.878
Right. Comedy lessons. Let's begin.

08:10.879 --> 08:13.445
I'm sorry. What is that noise?

08:13.447 --> 08:17.050
It's my bells, sire. I'm terrified.

08:17.051 --> 08:18.195
Don't be.

08:18.228 --> 08:20.374
I already told you
I've decided not to kill you.

08:20.489 --> 08:22.123
I mean, not that I don't want to.

08:22.123 --> 08:23.857
In fact, it would be mondo satisfying

08:23.858 --> 08:26.126
to cut your face off
and sew it back on inside out.

08:29.930 --> 08:32.030
Nah, I'll stick with my first plan.

08:32.032 --> 08:34.366
Teach me to be funny so I can woo my wife.

08:36.270 --> 08:37.837
Whatever you say, My King.

08:39.573 --> 08:42.308
♪ Comedy is easy
once you know the basics ♪

08:42.308 --> 08:44.777
♪ Starting with the concept of surprise ♪

08:44.778 --> 08:45.444
Right.

08:45.445 --> 08:47.947
♪ Take what folks
think, give it a wink ♪

08:47.948 --> 08:50.283
♪ You try it on now for size ♪

08:50.284 --> 08:51.718
- Me?
- Yeah.

08:56.290 --> 08:57.857
He was surprised.

08:57.858 --> 08:58.992
Uh...

08:58.993 --> 09:00.927
- ♪ Comedy gold ♪
- Really?

09:00.928 --> 09:02.996
♪ I'm telling you, it's comedy gold ♪

09:02.997 --> 09:03.963
Yes.

09:03.964 --> 09:05.064
♪ You're killing it ♪

09:05.065 --> 09:06.633
♪ If that doesn't slay 'em ♪

09:06.634 --> 09:07.900
♪ I'll murder you cold ♪

09:07.901 --> 09:11.004
♪ Swear to God, it's comedy gold ♪

09:11.005 --> 09:13.272
Well, our work here is done,
so I'll just be going.

09:13.273 --> 09:14.474
Oh, we're just getting started.

09:14.475 --> 09:16.976
- Ah, right.
- Lesson two!

09:16.977 --> 09:20.246
♪ Lesson number two is also fundamental ♪

09:20.247 --> 09:23.315
♪ Something that we call
"the rule of three" ♪

09:23.317 --> 09:26.486
♪ Set up the joke, give it a stroke ♪

09:26.487 --> 09:27.653
♪ Third time, bam ♪

09:27.654 --> 09:29.122
Yes! Now me!

09:29.123 --> 09:30.323
Three serfs walk into a bar.

09:30.324 --> 09:31.691
The first serf orders a hot grog.

09:31.692 --> 09:33.025
The second serf orders a hot grog.

09:33.026 --> 09:35.428
And the third serf orders a hot grog.

09:35.429 --> 09:38.983
But he has no money and neither do
the other two because they're serfs.

09:38.985 --> 09:39.985
Huh?

09:41.134 --> 09:42.435
♪ Comedy gold ♪

09:42.436 --> 09:46.038
- Yes! Nailed it!
- ♪ I promise you, it's comedy gold ♪

09:46.039 --> 09:47.607
♪ Hilarious ♪

09:47.608 --> 09:50.910
- ♪ The crowd will be rolling ♪
- ♪ Or heads will be rolled ♪

09:50.911 --> 09:52.678
♪ Oh, not with all this comedy gold ♪

09:52.679 --> 09:53.507
More, more!

09:53.509 --> 09:56.415
♪ Props can be a riot,
ethnic humor, can't deny it ♪

09:56.416 --> 09:59.018
♪ Or a pratfall,
if it's properly applied ♪

09:59.019 --> 10:02.888
♪ Depending on the viewer,
take it black or work it bluer ♪

10:02.889 --> 10:04.882
♪ Or try an observational aside ♪

10:05.625 --> 10:07.493
Have you ever noticed how lepers

10:07.494 --> 10:09.095
have pieces falling off of them?

10:09.096 --> 10:11.697
I mean, what's that all about?

10:12.699 --> 10:15.067
♪ Gonna be killer ♪

10:15.068 --> 10:17.636
♪ Gonna be ace ♪

10:17.637 --> 10:23.976
♪ Folks dying of laughter
all over the place ♪

10:23.977 --> 10:26.912
♪ And if I get desperate ♪

10:26.913 --> 10:29.348
♪ A pie in the face? ♪

10:29.349 --> 10:30.816
I dare you.

10:31.851 --> 10:34.920
♪ Telling you, it's comedy gold ♪

10:34.921 --> 10:37.823
Oh! You are a wonderful teacher.

10:37.824 --> 10:41.493
Perhaps now I shall finally be able to
satisfy my wife the same way you have.

10:43.398 --> 10:46.498
My God, we've got a strange relationship.

10:46.499 --> 10:48.634
♪ Telling you, it's comedy gold ♪

10:52.572 --> 10:54.540
Pirates, that's pomade.

10:54.541 --> 10:57.776
It's for relaxing my curls, not eating.

11:01.081 --> 11:03.348
Right, men.

11:03.348 --> 11:06.417
Let's stow this booty in the chest.

11:06.419 --> 11:08.220
Carl, give me the key.

11:11.758 --> 11:14.359
Oh, come on, guys. Not again.

11:14.360 --> 11:16.328
These idiots really stink
at being pirates.

11:16.329 --> 11:17.429
No kidding.

11:17.430 --> 11:18.831
Unbelievable.

11:18.832 --> 11:21.967
It's kind of nice being
on the same page, isn't it?

11:21.968 --> 11:23.902
It is nice to have a break

11:23.903 --> 11:25.971
from the relentless stream
of criticism, yeah.

11:25.972 --> 11:29.308
Maybe if you did things right,
I wouldn't have to say it.

11:29.309 --> 11:30.709
- Mouth breather.
- Egomaniac.

11:30.710 --> 11:32.277
And it's over.

11:32.278 --> 11:36.348
You. Walk with me.

11:37.817 --> 11:39.284
Oh, right. Of course.

