11:50.229 --> 11:51.530
Lads, could you give me a hand?

11:51.531 --> 11:52.631
Arr.

11:56.335 --> 12:00.604
You know, we met before, at Lilith Faire,

12:00.606 --> 12:02.841
the island of Lesbos.

12:02.842 --> 12:06.344
I looked a little different...
Fewer wrinkles.

12:06.345 --> 12:08.113
More like...

12:08.114 --> 12:09.614
Yes, of course.

12:09.615 --> 12:12.050
Well, you're Peter Pillager,
the pirate king.

12:12.767 --> 12:14.753
Well, your men used to be
the scourge of the seas.

12:15.888 --> 12:16.922
What happened there?

12:16.923 --> 12:18.523
Oh.

12:18.524 --> 12:21.393
You know how it is when you
spend too much time with people.

12:21.394 --> 12:23.528
Little things start to get to you...

12:23.529 --> 12:25.463
- Oh...
- And before you know it,

12:25.464 --> 12:27.432
it's all about who's taken whose booty.

12:27.433 --> 12:29.201
"It's my booty." "No, it's my booty."

12:29.202 --> 12:30.769
booty, booty, booty.

12:30.770 --> 12:33.305
- You stopped working together.
- Big-time.

12:33.306 --> 12:37.008
We can't even agree on how to
get our ship off that damn hill.

12:37.009 --> 12:41.313
The truth is...
I could do with a man like you.

12:41.314 --> 12:44.583
So I have a proposition.

12:44.584 --> 12:48.320
Either, "A," I kill all of you

12:48.321 --> 12:51.356
and keep that jewel
and the girls' supplies.

12:51.357 --> 12:56.294
- Why do you want the girls' supplies?
- Or "B," you join me and I let your squire

12:56.295 --> 12:59.264
and that annoying little
mouth breather go.

12:59.265 --> 13:01.700
Well, in all fairness to her,

13:01.701 --> 13:04.035
only 'cause she's not here
to defend herself,

13:04.036 --> 13:06.271
the mouth breathing
is a medical condition,

13:06.272 --> 13:09.507
- so she can't really help it.
- Seems like a pretty simple fix to me.

13:09.508 --> 13:11.476
Put food in mouth, close mouth, chew.

13:11.477 --> 13:13.578
What kind of moron can't do that?

13:15.381 --> 13:18.183
Again, not to get into semantics here,

13:18.184 --> 13:21.286
but if she closes her mouth
while she eats,

13:21.287 --> 13:24.589
she's literally not breathing
out of anywhere.

13:24.590 --> 13:25.757
You get used to it.

13:25.758 --> 13:28.860
Honestly, lately, I can't fall asleep
until she starts snoring.

13:28.861 --> 13:31.162
Dude, you're making me uncomfortable.

13:31.163 --> 13:33.565
Who are you choosing,
me or the mouth breather?

13:33.566 --> 13:37.001
Call her a "mouth breather" one more time.

13:37.002 --> 13:39.237
Mouth breather.

13:39.238 --> 13:41.706
How did you do that?

13:41.707 --> 13:43.641
I keep trying to tell everyone...

13:43.642 --> 13:44.809
Oh.

13:44.810 --> 13:47.345
I'm not just the guy
that eats the raisins.

13:50.082 --> 13:52.050
Excuse me, excuse me.

13:52.051 --> 13:54.986
Chef coming through. Thank you.
This way, my lady.

13:54.987 --> 13:56.788
Here's your table, My Queen.

13:56.789 --> 13:59.757
What fresh idiocy does king
Richard have in store for me now?

13:59.758 --> 14:01.392
Um, I'm...

14:01.393 --> 14:03.361
That was rhetorical. Shoo.

14:03.362 --> 14:06.297
Chef out.

14:07.766 --> 14:09.467
Welcome to the show!

14:09.468 --> 14:12.437
I introduce to you, without further ado,

14:12.438 --> 14:13.905
the king of comedy!

14:13.906 --> 14:17.222
Hello! Thank you very, very, very much.

14:17.224 --> 14:19.177
Now, I understand you've all come here

14:19.178 --> 14:22.113
under threat of death,
and I appreciate it.

14:22.114 --> 14:24.649
In fact... I ordered it.

14:27.419 --> 14:29.320
Everybody laugh!

14:30.923 --> 14:32.581
What on God's flat earth is going on?

14:32.583 --> 14:35.193
Well, they say the way to a woman's heart

14:35.194 --> 14:38.183
- is through her funny bone, so...
- Oh, God. Let's not do this.

14:38.185 --> 14:41.132
Why did the king go to the dentist?

14:41.133 --> 14:42.533
To get his teeth crowned.

14:42.534 --> 14:44.691
To get his teeth crowned.
Uh, you've heard that one.

14:44.693 --> 14:47.004
Mm! "You might be a peasant" jokes.

14:47.005 --> 14:51.275
If you have more children than teeth,

14:51.276 --> 14:53.911
you might be a peasant.

14:56.615 --> 14:58.783
Is this thing on?

14:58.784 --> 15:02.219
Ugh. He's dying out there.
Give him the pie.

15:02.220 --> 15:03.721
Now?!

15:03.722 --> 15:05.523
That's the big finale.

15:05.524 --> 15:07.692
Damn it, man, look at the poor bastard.

15:07.693 --> 15:09.160
Give him the pie.

15:09.161 --> 15:15.488
If your toilet is a tree,
then you might be...

15:22.207 --> 15:25.342
She laughed! It worked! She laughed!

15:25.343 --> 15:28.846
Quick, give me more pies so I can
keep hitting Gareth in the face.

15:28.847 --> 15:32.277
Or someone else. I-I can pie someone else.

15:34.448 --> 15:35.448
You're a fool.

15:35.449 --> 15:37.116
When my men see me captive,

15:37.117 --> 15:39.618
they will swarm on you like hornets.

15:39.619 --> 15:40.953
No. Bees.

15:40.954 --> 15:42.121
No, hornets was better.

15:42.122 --> 15:43.622
Well, you can let them try,

15:43.623 --> 15:46.386
but I'll be damned if I'm letting my team
end up like yours.

15:46.388 --> 15:49.628
So I'm gonna rescue them,
rouse us to work together,

15:49.629 --> 15:51.831
defeat your... hold on.

15:52.933 --> 15:55.501
Oh, for the love of Mike, what happened?

15:55.502 --> 15:56.835
Sid was right.

15:56.836 --> 15:59.171
It was time to stop bickering
and work together.

15:59.172 --> 16:00.673
So we did, and we overthrew the camp.

16:00.674 --> 16:04.410
You missed an amazing battle,
better than anything at castle black.

16:04.411 --> 16:07.179
Well, FYI, I was also gonna come back,

16:07.180 --> 16:09.448
and I was gonna suggest that
we start working together, too,

16:09.449 --> 16:10.849
- wasn't I? Tell them.
- Oh, please, stop.

16:10.850 --> 16:12.484
This whole time, I've been
saying that I was gonna...

16:12.485 --> 16:16.455
- This is all a little humiliating.
- You know what? Doesn't matter.

16:16.456 --> 16:18.023
I know we've been
driving each other crazy,

16:18.024 --> 16:20.092
but I think we've got something
really good going on here.

16:20.093 --> 16:23.195
I mean, look at us...
We're gorgeous, very diverse.

16:23.195 --> 16:27.665
I think if we pull it together, we could
do something great, legendary even.

16:27.667 --> 16:30.335
What do you say?

16:30.336 --> 16:31.703
We are diverse.

16:32.939 --> 16:35.174
Super diverse.

16:35.175 --> 16:37.843
I remember when we had something special.

16:37.844 --> 16:39.611
Arr.

16:39.612 --> 16:40.972
I miss us.

16:41.948 --> 16:44.616
Now, look, either we can take
your pirate supplies...

16:44.617 --> 16:46.385
The swords, the hooks...

16:46.386 --> 16:47.386
- Parrots.
- Booty.

16:47.387 --> 16:48.854
- Peg legs.
- Girls' supplies.

16:48.855 --> 16:51.356
Yes, yes, all of it,
or we can work together

16:51.357 --> 16:56.028
to get your ship off that hill
and you can take us to Valencia.

16:56.029 --> 16:57.062
What do you say?

17:04.037 --> 17:06.338
Did I just cut your hand?

17:06.339 --> 17:08.707
Yes. Very badly.

17:08.708 --> 17:10.509
Sorry.

17:16.082 --> 17:17.749
Where are you going?

17:17.750 --> 17:19.584
It's time for 4:00 fool-around.

17:19.585 --> 17:20.660
Is it?

17:20.662 --> 17:23.922
M-my sundial must be slow
because of the... c-clouds.

17:23.923 --> 17:26.590
If you're worried I'm upset
about you helping my husband

17:26.592 --> 17:28.827
with that ridiculous show, then don't be.

17:28.828 --> 17:31.997
Who cares? He's an idiot.

17:31.998 --> 17:33.598
Yes, well, that's the thing.

17:33.599 --> 17:35.233
I don't think I can do this anymore.

17:35.234 --> 17:39.938
I guess I just feel a little... guilty.

17:39.939 --> 17:41.606
Well, that's very noble of you

17:41.607 --> 17:43.875
to care about someone's feelings.

17:43.876 --> 17:45.839
Guards!

17:45.841 --> 17:48.511
If you're developing a conscience,
then you're no good to me.

17:48.513 --> 17:50.949
Take him to the dungeon,
the really scary one.

17:50.950 --> 17:52.117
With the mice.

17:52.118 --> 17:53.284
Wait, no! Please!

17:53.285 --> 17:54.953
At least let me change my clothes!

17:54.954 --> 17:57.455
These are gang colors!

17:57.456 --> 17:59.958
Oh, hello.

17:59.959 --> 18:01.226
I was just coming to see Steve.

18:01.227 --> 18:02.727
Who's Steve?

18:02.728 --> 18:05.363
Steve McKinzie. The jester.

18:05.364 --> 18:07.932
You don't know his name?

18:07.933 --> 18:09.567
Well, no matter.

18:09.568 --> 18:13.738
Say, what do you call
a tiny mosquito in a tin suit?

18:13.739 --> 18:15.573
- Oh, God.
- Nope.

18:15.574 --> 18:17.575
A <i> gnat</i> in shining armor.

18:17.576 --> 18:20.645
- I've got so many of these.
- Please stop talking.

18:20.646 --> 18:22.247
No, I love talking with you.

18:22.248 --> 18:24.582
Right, you maggots!

18:24.583 --> 18:27.485
Let's get this boat off the hill.

18:27.486 --> 18:29.787
What?

18:29.788 --> 18:32.790
It's just nice to hear you
call us "maggots" again.

18:32.791 --> 18:35.627
You've always been maggots in here.

18:35.628 --> 18:37.595
Arr!

18:37.596 --> 18:39.497
Prepare the lines!

18:45.671 --> 18:48.239
♪ we heave together, we ho together ♪

18:48.240 --> 18:50.308
♪ All working toe to toe together ♪

18:50.309 --> 18:52.076
♪ Ahoy, look out below together! ♪

18:52.077 --> 18:53.945
Run away! Run away!

18:56.348 --> 18:58.683
♪ Now off together,
we'll cruise together ♪

18:58.684 --> 19:01.018
♪ With pirate stuff we'll use together ♪

19:01.019 --> 19:03.254
♪ Guys, we should get tattoos together ♪

19:03.255 --> 19:04.422
Arr!

19:06.492 --> 19:09.660
♪ And, together, look what we can do ♪

19:09.661 --> 19:11.929
♪ Together we're one scurvy crew ♪

19:11.930 --> 19:13.863
- ♪ Together, we're not bad ♪
- ♪ It's true ♪

19:13.865 --> 19:16.134
My God, just get a room, you two.

19:16.135 --> 19:22.974
♪ Togetherness will see us
through to the end ♪

19:22.975 --> 19:25.543
Land ho!

19:25.544 --> 19:27.044
"Land ho," indeed, Carl.

19:32.284 --> 19:33.618
Gal...

19:33.619 --> 19:34.952
Can I call you "Gal"?

19:34.953 --> 19:36.487
Uh, well, I don't love it.

19:36.488 --> 19:39.323
I have to talk to you.

19:39.324 --> 19:40.858
I feel a little guilty about something.

19:40.859 --> 19:43.127
Actually, so do I.

19:43.128 --> 19:45.496
I stashed a bag of trail mix
before we left.

19:46.665 --> 19:47.999
Raisins intact.

19:48.000 --> 19:49.400
Really?

19:49.401 --> 19:50.568
Knock yourself out.

19:50.569 --> 19:52.636
And feel free to eat with your mouth open.

19:52.637 --> 19:54.305
It's not as gross as I make it out to be.

19:54.306 --> 19:58.008
I mean, it's gross,
but it's not gross-gross.

19:59.644 --> 20:02.680
Listen, Galavant,

20:02.681 --> 20:05.349
I think the reason
I've been so difficult recently

20:05.350 --> 20:09.019
is that I was villainizing you
so I felt better about myself.

20:09.020 --> 20:13.190
I'm probably signing my parents' death
warrant by telling you this, but...

20:13.191 --> 20:14.525
I lied.

20:14.526 --> 20:17.061
I'm leading you into a trap.

20:19.503 --> 20:20.931
Galavant?

20:20.932 --> 20:22.666
We're almost there.

20:22.667 --> 20:25.169
Did you hear anything I just said?

20:25.170 --> 20:27.171
Sorry.

20:27.172 --> 20:29.519
I don't always listen when you talk.

20:29.520 --> 20:31.371
I will get better in that.

20:31.373 --> 20:32.847
***

20:32.848 --> 20:34.848
Your parents or something?

20:36.097 --> 20:38.091
I look foward to see them.

20:38.092 --> 20:41.292
Right. Yeah, parents are the best.

20:42.448 --> 20:44.878
***

20:44.879 --> 20:46.472
To Valencia!

20:46.473 --> 20:48.473
Arr!

20:50.449 --> 20:52.449
I'm coming, my love.

